from sklearn import metrics
import warnings

warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')
In [14]:
# splitting the dataframe into 2 dataframes randomly, a train set of 70% and a test set of 30%
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df[['sepal length (cm)', 'sepal width (cm)', 'petal length (cm)',
       'petal width (cm)']],df[['target']] , test_size=0.30, random_state=101)
In [15]:
model = svm.SVC()
model.fit(X_train,y_train)
y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
print(metrics.accuracy_score(y_pred,y_test));
